@caliope76
Generally when you crack a game like The Sims 3, you do not start the game from the launcher to prevent the game from automatically updating thus removing the crack that allows you to play without a disc. I recommend always starting from the executable(.exe file) you replace when installing the crack, both for this and for other games you might play in the future.

@Legend.Cyrus
Question. When you got this error: "Update of Sims3 failed, Setup is unable to continue", were you already using the cracked files, or did you put back the original (un-cracked) ones?

As far as I know, updates or patches for sims 3 will not work if the installed game contains cracked content.

@Legend.Cyrus
The "Your disc is not a valid copy, please contact support" results from attempting to play the game without cracking it first. 

I recommend going to GameCopyWorld (google it) and getting the Town Life Stuff fixed image. It allows you to play without replacing files which means you can always update to the latest patch and play without issues. All you need to do is mount it and you can play.

@RottenMango

When you click the start menu, it will show a place for you to type in words. Type in the word regedit

This will open up a tab called Registry Editor that has a list of folders in it. First click the folder called "HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE." You will see subfolders. Click the one called "Software". You will see more subfolders. Click the one called "Sims". You will see the subfolder "The Sims 3". Click it. Now on the right screen you will see a list of things. Double click the one called SKU. It will display a pop-up that allows you to change a number value. Remember the original number just in case this doesn't work .... Change the number value to 2...if that does not work use any number between 1-7 until it works

@delirioushatred, TS3 & TS3host.dll are the only ones you need to copy, however it's not an issue if you copy the other file as this is the keygen.

